Hi <@U8MPCDJAY>, <@U7THT3TM3> and I are updating SossMLJ.jl and I was seeing this error:
```Precompiling project...
  Progress [========================================>]  2/2
  ✗ Soss
  ✗ SossMLJ
0 dependencies successfully precompiled in 41 seconds (156 already precompiled)
2 dependencies errored
     Testing Running tests...
┌ Warning: Replacing module `Distributions`
└ @ Base loading.jl:937
┌ Warning: Module Distributions with build ID 2515122799789711 is missing from the cache.
│ This may mean Distributions [31c24e10-a181-5473-b8eb-7969acd0382f] does not support precompilation but is imported by a module that does.
└ @ Base loading.jl:1008```
I think it was working ok, but I recently updated to 1.6 (from 1.6-rc1). I have no idea if that's what caused the problem, but deleting the compiled `Distributions` got it to rebuild just fine. So I can't replicate the error now, but Dilum thought you might still want to know about it.
